 It'll be much easier to work out what is going on.
 The standard delay module has many features compared to standalone delay
 pedals!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Connect a module
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
You'll now want to connect up the delay.
 Hold input 1, then with another finger tap the delay you've added.
 This multi touch stuff is really much easier to see on a video.
 Any recent video should show this connection style.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
This is just the same as connecting up pedals on a pedal board, but you
 can split and merge signals easily.
 You choose a source and then a module to connect to.
 So now hold delay 1 and then tap output 1 to connect them.
 If you're connecting things with multiple inputs or outputs a screen will
 appear where you can select which to use.
 
